=&\frac{(y-x)^2(y-z) + (z-y)^2(x-y) + (x-z)^2(z-x)}{(y-z)(z-x)(x-y)(y-z)}
\end{align*}

To make the expression easier to work with, we can let $a=y-x$, $b=z-y$, and $c=x-z$. Then our expression becomes:

$$\frac{a^2(y-z) + b^2(x-y) + c^2(z-x)}{(y-z)(z-x)(x-y)(y-z)}$$

To minimize this expression, we can try to make the numerator as small as possible.

